This Readme contains information how to install and use our galaxy42 network for Ubuntu(tested on 16.04 LTS).

1) Compiler
	sudo add-apt-repository ppa:ubuntu-toolchain-r/test
	sudo apt-get update
	sudo apt-get install gcc-5 g++-5

	sudo update-alternatives --install /usr/bin/gcc gcc /usr/bin/gcc-5 60 --slave /usr/bin/g++ g++ /usr/bin/g++-5

2) Install Sodium and Boost:
	sudo apt-get install libsodium-dev libboost-all-dev

3) Install other dependences:
	sudo apt-get install cmake autoconf pkg-config libtool libfftw3-dev build-essential
		* libfftw3-dev -  fast Fourier transform (FFT) alghoritm library used in ntru cryptography

4) Clone project from git-repository, enter project directory and change branch to usable_proxy_nocrypto:
	git clone https://github.com/tigusoft-vm/antinet
	cd antinet
	git checkout usable_proxy_nocrypto

5) Initialize and update submodules:
	git submodule init
	git submodule update

6) Change directory to galaxy42:
	cd galaxy42

7) Make project, you can do it for 2 different ways:

	5.1)First is not very secure so we recomend to use it only for Virtual Machines:
		sudo cmake . && make
	Using this method requied running script as a root.

	5.2)Second way is to install script called "install" which is placed in galaxy42/script/install-as-root and install it as a root:
		cd script/install-as-root
		sudo ./install
	Then go back to galaxy42, run cmake and make
		cd ../..
		cmake . && make
	This is safe method but can contain bugs.
